# Conflict Early Warning System - Dashboard Specification

## Project Overview
- **Name**: Conflict Early Warning System (CEWS)
- **Type**: Real-time intelligence monitoring dashboard
- **Core Functionality**: Displays triggered intelligence briefs with threat scores, live OSINT feeds, and geographic risk visualization
- **Target Users**: Security analysts, intelligence teams at SunHacks 2K26

## Visual & Rendering Specification

### Theme & Colors
- **Background Primary**: `#0a0e1a` (deep navy)
- **Background Secondary**: `#111827` (card backgrounds)
- **Background Tertiary**: `#1f2937` (elevated elements)
- **Accent Primary**: `#00f0ff` (cyan glow)
- **Accent Secondary**: `#3b82f6` (blue highlights)
- **Danger/High Threat**: `#ef4444` (red)
- **Warning/Medium Threat**: `#f59e0b` (amber)
- **Success/Low Threat**: `#22c55e` (green)
- **Text Primary**: `#f9fafb`
- **Text Secondary**: `#9ca3af`
- **Text Muted**: `#6b7280`

### Typography
- **Font Family**: Inter (Google Fonts), fallback: system-ui, sans-serif
- **Headings**: Bold, tracking-tight
- **Body**: Regular weight, leading-relaxed
- **Monospace elements**: JetBrains Mono for data/numbers

### Layout
- 7-column responsive grid system
- Header spans full width
- Main content: 3-column layout (Alert Panel 60% | Feed 40%)
- Gap between grid elements: 6 (24px)

## Components

### 1. Header
- Project title: "Conflict Early Warning System" with shield icon
- System status indicator: Green pulsing dot + "SYSTEM ACTIVE"
- Time to Last Signal countdown (mm:ss format, updates live)

### 2. Alert Panel (Primary)
- Section title: "TRIGGERED BRIEFS" with warning badge count
- Scrollable list of BriefCards
- Each BriefCard contains:
  - Circular gauge showing Composite Threat Score (0-10)
  - Signal velocity indicator (trending up/down arrow + percentage)
  - Brief title
  - Top 3 entities (actors/locations) as chips
  - Timestamp
  - "Source Traceability" expandable button
  - Severity-based left border color

### 3. BriefCard Details
- **Threat Score Gauge**: SVG circular progress, color-coded
  - 0-4: Green
  - 5-6: Amber
  - 7-8: Orange
  - 9-10: Red with pulse animation
- **Signal Velocity**: Arrow icon + percentage change
- **Entities**: Pills with icons (user for actors, map-pin for locations)
- **Source Traceability**: Click reveals list of cited URLs

### 4. Intelligence Feed (Sidebar)
- Section title: "LIVE INTELLIGENCE FEED"
- Source badges: X, Reddit, NewsAPI, Telegram with distinct colors
- Auto-scrolling feed items (newest at top)
- Each item shows: source icon, content snippet, timestamp, sentiment indicator

### 5. Geographic Heatmap (Placeholder)
- Styled container with gradient background
- "REGIONAL RISK CONCENTRATION" header
- Grid pattern suggesting a map
- Hotspot indicators (pulsing circles)
- Mock coordinates and region labels

### 6. Intelligence Brief Modal
- Overlay with backdrop blur
- Executive Summary section
- Sentiment Hostility Rating (visual bar)
- Pattern Match Signature (highlighted text)
- Close button
- Animation: scale + fade in

## Interaction Specification

### User Controls
- Click BriefCard → Opens Intelligence Brief Modal
- Click "Source Traceability" → Expands URL list inline
- Hover on cards → Subtle glow effect
- Close modal → Click X or backdrop

### Animations
- Pulse animation on high threat scores (>= 9)
- Smooth transitions (300ms ease)
- Feed items slide in from right
- Modal scales in (0.95 → 1.0)

## Mock Data Structure

### Briefs Array
```javascript
{
  id: string,
  title: string,
  threatScore: number (0-10),
  signalVelocity: number (percentage change),
  entities: { actors: string[], locations: string[] },
  timestamp: Date,
  sources: string[],
  summary: string,
  sentimentHostility: number (0-100),
  patternMatch: string
}
```

### Feed Items Array
```javascript
{
  id: string,
  source: 'X' | 'Reddit' | 'NewsAPI' | 'Telegram',
  content: string,
  timestamp: Date,
  sentiment: 'positive' | 'negative' | 'neutral'
}
```

## Technical Stack
- React 18
- Vite
- Tailwind CSS 3
- Lucide React (icons)
- No additional UI libraries

## Acceptance Criteria
1. Dashboard renders with all 4 main sections (Header, Alert Panel, Feed, Heatmap)
2. Mock data displays immediately with no API calls
3. Modal opens on card click with all details
4. Source traceability expands/collapses
5. Live feed shows scrolling items
6. Threat gauges display correct colors per score
7. Responsive layout works on desktop (1024px+)
8. All interactive elements have hover/active states
9. No console errors on load
